.TH "usb_add_gadget_udc_release" 9 "usb_add_gadget_udc_release" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_add_gadget_udc_release \- adds a new gadget to the udc class driver list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_add_gadget_udc_release
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "struct usb_gadget *gadget "  ","
.BI "void (*release)(struct device *dev) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
the parent device to this udc. Usually the controller driver's
device.
.IP "gadget" 12
the gadget to be added to the list.
.IP "release" 12
a gadget release function.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero on success, negative errno otherwise.
Calls the gadget release function in the latter case.
